		<div class="post" id="post-4651088">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4651088)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4651088">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="3146689"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1589703953 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">17 May 2020 08:25</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4651088">
									

<p>I'm a bit conflicted here. On one hand, this is fairly well-written and the pacing is fine in most places (although some parts could use a but of trimming), the creature itself is also pretty cool in its origin. It has certain atmosphere to it.</p>
<p>On the other? As others have pointed out, the ending is pretty dull compared to the buildup, instead of providing some scary implication or new information for us to theorise, it simply retells the thing's effects, as it was already mentioned that folks could see him IRL and that last occurrence wasn't vastly different from anything that came before it.</p>
<p>The dream section also felt kinda lacking. It's really nothing new to have nightmares about a scary monster eating children, with the location also being very typical for this type of dreams. It might've been a good opportunity for the cyclops to shine, but he just behaves like a regular murder monster.</p>
<p>I'll stick with novote on this one.</p>
<p>UPD: The new ending is better than the previous one, admittedly. I'll think about this more, but I do think it's heading in the right direction.</p>

							</div>

								
